{
  "nodes": [
    {
      "id": "bootstrap",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## bootstrap.Run()\n`internal/bootstrap/bootstrap.go`\n\n- Builds registry, key store, config\n- Creates `*Gateway`\n- Calls `httpserver.NewRouter(..., gw, ...)`",
      "x": -920,
      "y": -680,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "new-router",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## NewRouter(...)\n`internal/httpserver/router.go:31`\n\n- `ensureGateway(gw, registry)`\n- `chi.NewRouter()`\n- Middleware stack\n- **mountOpenAIRoutes(r, gw, ...)**",
      "x": -920,
      "y": -460,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "middleware",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Global chi stack\n`router.go:52–68`\n\n- OTel, logging, recover\n- CORS, rate-limit",
      "x": -920,
      "y": -220,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 160,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "mount-openai",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## mountOpenAIRoutes()\n`router.go:194`\n\n- ProxyAuth middleware\n- **POST /v1/chat/completions**\n- GET /v1/models, other /v1/*",
      "x": -920,
      "y": 0,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "post-route",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## POST /v1/chat/completions\n`router.go:200`\n\n`r.Post(..., handler.ChatCompletions(gw))`\n\n- Auth required\n- Closes over `*Gateway`",
      "x": -920,
      "y": 240,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "4"
    },
    {
      "id": "gateway",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## *aigateway.Gateway\n`gateway.go:51`\n\n- RWMutex + provider map\n- Strategy + plugins\n- `Route(ctx, req)`\n- `RouteStream(ctx, req)`\n- FindByModel / FindStreamingByModel",
      "x": -920,
      "y": 480,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 220,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "chat-completions",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## ChatCompletions(gw)\n`internal/handler/chat.go:14`\n\n1. `DecodeChatCompletionRequest(r.Body)`\n2. `req.Validate()`\n3. Branch on `req.Stream`",
      "x": -500,
      "y": 160,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "decode",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## DecodeChatCompletionRequest\n`internal/handler/chatrequest.go:87`\n\n- Pool get wire DTO\n- JSON decode\n- Map messages\n- Return `providers.Request`",
      "x": -100,
      "y": 40,
      "width": 340,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "wire-dto",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## routeChatCompletionRequest\n`chatrequest.go:13`\n\nWire DTO — 19 fields\nBoth token fields copied out",
      "x": 320,
      "y": 340,
      "width": 260,
      "height": 160,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "validate",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## req.Validate()\n`providers/core/chat.go:192`\n\n- model, messages required\n- `max_tokens > 0`\n- **`max_completion_tokens > 0`**",
      "x": 320,
      "y": 80,
      "width": 260,
      "height": 180,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "error-node",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## apierror.WriteOpenAI\n\n400 decode / validation\n400 model not found\nRoute errors",
      "x": 320,
      "y": -180,
      "width": 260,
      "height": 160,
      "color": "1"
    },
    {
      "id": "request-obj",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## providers.Request\n`providers/core/chat.go:149`\n\n**Output limits (#141):**\n- `MaxTokens` → `\"max_tokens\"`\n- `MaxCompletionTokens` → `\"max_completion_tokens\"`\n\nAlso: Model, Messages, Stream, Tools…\n\n✅ Both survive decode + validation\n❌ Drop happens in provider layer",
      "x": -460,
      "y": 440,
      "width": 380,
      "height": 280,
      "color": "3"
    },
    {
      "id": "fork-label",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**if req.Stream**",
      "x": -260,
      "y": 780,
      "width": 160,
      "height": 60,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "streaming",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## req.Stream == true\n`chat.go:27–44`\n\n- FindByModel\n- FindStreamingByModel\n- **RouteStream(ctx, req)**\n- sse.Write\n- Provider-aware path resolves StreamProvider before CompleteStream",
      "x": -860,
      "y": 860,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "non-streaming",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## req.Stream == false\n`chat.go:47–64`\n\n- FindByModel\n- **Route(ctx, req)**\n- JSON encode response\n- Provider resolution happens inside strategy execution",
      "x": 0,
      "y": 860,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "note",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**Issue #141 checkpoint:**\nBoth token fields ride into Route / RouteStream unchanged. Drop is per-provider payload mapping.",
      "x": -460,
      "y": 860,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 140,
      "color": "3"
    },
    {
      "id": "provider-blind-slot",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Normalize before provider resolution?\n`handler/chat.go:21–53 or gateway.go:422–486`\n\n- Request is only `providers.Request`\n- Final provider is not known for fallback/load-balance/cost strategies\n- Can globally coalesce: if `MaxTokens == nil`, copy `MaxCompletionTokens`\n- Cannot honestly be non-OpenAI-only at this point",
      "x": 0,
      "y": 1180,
      "width": 340,
      "height": 240,
      "color": "3"
    },
    {
      "id": "route-nonstream",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Gateway.Route(ctx, req)\n`gateway.go:397`\n\n- Starts root span\n- Resolves model alias\n- `g.getStrategy()`\n- Runs before-request plugins\n- `s.Execute(ctx, req)`",
      "x": 380,
      "y": 860,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 220,
      "color": "2"
    },
    {
      "id": "get-strategy",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## getStrategy() lookup closure\n`gateway.go:890`\n\n- Snapshots `g.providers`\n- Builds `lookup(name)`\n- Circuit breaker wrapper may replace provider\n- Does not inspect token-limit fields",
      "x": 740,
      "y": 860,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 220,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "strategy-execute",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Strategy.Execute(ctx, req)\n`internal/strategies/*.go`\n\n- Single: lookup then `p.Complete(ctx, req)`\n- Fallback: loops targets, supports-model check, retries\n- Load/latency/cost choose provider before call\n- First non-stream provider-aware seam",
      "x": 1100,
      "y": 860,
      "width": 340,
      "height": 240,
      "color": "6"
    },
    {
      "id": "route-stream",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Gateway.RouteStream(ctx, req)\n`gateway.go:1163`\n\n- Starts stream span\n- Resolves model alias\n- Runs before-request plugins\n- Resolves streaming provider order",
      "x": -860,
      "y": 1180,
      "width": 300,
      "height": 220,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "stream-provider-resolved",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## resolveStreamingProviderLocked(req)\n`gateway.go:1237–1279`\n\n- Uses strategy mode to order target keys\n- Finds a provider implementing `StreamProvider`\n- Provider name is known before `sp.CompleteStream(ctx, req)`\n- Stream-side provider-aware seam",
      "x": -500,
      "y": 1180,
      "width": 340,
      "height": 240,
      "color": "5"
    },
    {
      "id": "provider-mapping",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "## Non-OpenAI provider payload mapping\n`providers/*/*.go`\n\n- Most providers build outbound structs from `req.MaxTokens`\n- Examples: Mistral, Anthropic, Bedrock, Gemini, Replicate\n- `MaxCompletionTokens` is already on the request but is not read\n- OpenAI non-streaming marshals the whole request; streaming uses SDK params",
      "x": 740,
      "y": 1240,
      "width": 380,
      "height": 260,
      "color": "3"
    },
    {
      "id": "provider-aware-note",
      "type": "text",
      "text": "**Answer to before provider resolution:**\nIf the rule must be non-OpenAI-only, it cannot be fully provider-blind. Put it after lookup / before `Complete`, in a provider wrapper, or inside each provider mapper. If global coalescing is acceptable, do it once before provider selection.",
      "x": 1160,
      "y": 1240,
      "width": 340,
      "height": 200,
      "color": "3"
    }
  ],
